  "text": "The VM genes belong to a family of homologous virulence-related genes originally identified in L. interrogans and modulate the pathogenesis of L. interrogans in humans [CITATION_1] . These genes in B. bacilliformis, B. australis, and B. ancashensis, but not in other Bartonella spp., the further comparative analysis and functional studies on these VM proteins and the large number of other hypothetical proteins in Bartonella spp. will shed light on the pathogenesis mechanisms of bartonellosis, which are so far largely unknown.",
